# Cursor AI Rules for Property Portal Project

## Git Workflow
- Always commit changes with descriptive messages
- Push to GitHub after committing
- Use conventional commit messages: "feat:", "fix:", "docs:", "refactor:"
- Never commit sensitive data (.env files, passwords, etc.)

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow Next.js 14 App Router conventions
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Maintain luxury black theme with gold/amber accents

## Database
- Use Prisma ORM for database operations
- Always handle errors gracefully
- Use transactions for multi-step operations
- Validate data before database operations

## File Structure
- Keep components in `/components` directory
- API routes in `/app/api` directory
- Use route groups for organization: `(admin)`, `(auth)`, `(public)`

## Security
- Never expose API keys or secrets
- Validate user input
- Use NextAuth for authentication
- Implement proper role-based access control

## Performance
- Use dynamic imports for large components
- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use Suspense boundaries where needed


